Availability Set vs Availability Zone (Azure VM)
Availability Set

Protects against server/rack failure inside a single datacenter to avoid single point of failure
VMs distributed across:

Fault Domains → different racks/power/network
Update Domains → different maintenance groups


Suitable for applications running within one datacenter
SLA: 99.95% when properly configured
Lower latency between VMs because they stay in the same datacenter. [learn.microsoft.com], [bing.com]

Availability Zone

Protects against entire datacenter failure
VMs deployed across physically separate datacenters within the same Azure region
Each zone has independent:

Power
Cooling
Network


Suitable for mission-critical production applications
SLA: 99.99%
Higher resiliency than Availability Sets. [learn.microsoft.com], [bing.com]

Simple Comparison
Availability Set

Same region ✅
Same datacenter ✅
Different racks ✅
Datacenter failure protection ❌
Lower cost ✅

Availability Zone

Same region ✅
Different datacenters ✅
Different power/network ✅
Datacenter failure protection ✅
Higher availability ✅ 

Example
Availability Set

VM1 → Rack 1
VM2 → Rack 2
If Rack 1 fails → VM2 still running

Availability Zone

VM1 → Zone 1 (Datacenter A)
VM2 → Zone 2 (Datacenter B)
If Datacenter A fails → VM2 still running

