What is VMSS?
VMSS = A service that creates and manages multiple identical VMs automatically.
Instead of creating:
VM1
VM2
VM3
VM4

manually, you create one VMSS, and Azure manages all VMs for you.

Why Use VMSS?
Auto Scaling

Automatically adds VMs when load increases
Automatically removes VMs when load decreases

Example:
CPU > 70% → Add 2 VMs
CPU < 30% → Remove 2 VMs

Uniform Configuration
All VMs use:
Same image
Same OS
Same application
Same configuration

Main Components
VM Image
Template used to create VMs.

Scale Rules
-- Rules that decide when to add/remove VMs.
   Example:
   -- CPU based
   -- Memory based
   -- Schedule based


Scaling Types
Manual Scaling
Auto Scaling

VMSS vs Availability Set
Availability Set
-- Prevents hardware failures
-- Fixed number of VMs
